WEBVTT

00:11.708 --> 00:15.750
( drumroll  )

00:15.750 --> 00:18.417
( rousing orchestral
fanfare playing  )

00:28.583 --> 00:30.375
( fanfare ends  )

00:32.083 --> 00:36.542
( funky disco beat plays  )

00:36.542 --> 00:37.291
( clinking  )

00:44.917 --> 00:48.959
( clinking  )

00:51.834 --> 00:54.625
( clinking  )

00:54.625 --> 00:56.583
♪ Indulging inaccuracy ♪

00:56.583 --> 00:58.959
♪ I'm picking apart
my friend Lizzie ♪

00:58.959 --> 01:02.834
♪ Throw another word on me
and watch me hurl it back ♪

01:02.834 --> 01:05.041
♪ I know you, I swear I do ♪

01:05.041 --> 01:08.792
♪ You're just like me,
you're sipping a cup of pity ♪

01:08.792 --> 01:11.166
♪ Ah... ♪

01:11.166 --> 01:14.125
♪ Did I forget to mention
I'm the center of attention ♪

01:14.125 --> 01:16.667
♪ In my universe
my pain's my pension ♪

01:16.667 --> 01:19.125
♪ Ooh... ♪

01:19.125 --> 01:22.125
♪ I know you, I swear I do ♪

01:22.125 --> 01:25.125
♪ You're just like me, you're
sipping a cup of dreams ♪

01:25.125 --> 01:26.708
( grunting  )

01:26.708 --> 01:28.333
♪ Yeah... ♪

01:28.333 --> 01:30.750
♪ Soul sloshing,
don't shush me ♪

01:30.750 --> 01:34.708
♪ Just listen to me, pretty
little kitty in the sky ♪

01:34.708 --> 01:35.917
( grunts  )

01:35.917 --> 01:39.708
( grunting  )

01:39.708 --> 01:43.875
♪ Sweet is my... surprise ♪

01:43.875 --> 01:45.458
♪ Oh... ♪
( grunting  )

01:48.708 --> 01:53.208
( panting  )

01:55.917 --> 01:58.625
( marker squeaking  )

02:05.917 --> 02:07.834
( phone rings musically  )

02:09.708 --> 02:11.041
Oh, no.

02:11.041 --> 02:12.041
( ringing musically  )

02:14.708 --> 02:17.750
( ringing continues  )

02:17.750 --> 02:20.125
( gasps  )
( clinking  )

02:20.125 --> 02:20.750
( ringing continues  )

02:23.875 --> 02:25.542
( clanking  )
( whooshing  )

02:27.959 --> 02:29.375
( clanking  )
( whooshing  )

02:32.000 --> 02:34.875
( grunts  )

02:34.875 --> 02:36.375
( ringing continues  )
( grunts  )

02:38.625 --> 02:39.708
Hi, Mom.

02:39.708 --> 02:41.834
Hello, Madeline.
What are you doing?

02:41.834 --> 02:44.792
Uh... homework.

02:44.792 --> 02:46.875
Over spring break?

02:46.875 --> 02:48.417
( on phone  ):
You're not climbing, are you?

02:48.417 --> 02:50.083
'Cause you know I don't
want you to be climbing.

02:50.083 --> 02:53.375
No, Mom, I'm not climbing.

02:53.375 --> 02:55.542
Mrs. Phillips, they've
been waiting for you.

02:55.542 --> 02:57.291
Just... I'm sorry,
just one second.

02:57.291 --> 02:58.834
Um, sweetie, I'm going
to be a little late.

02:58.834 --> 03:00.166
So I'm going
to need you to...

03:00.166 --> 03:02.458
Pick up Max from day care.
Surprise.

03:02.458 --> 03:04.041
Yeah, it's not going
to be forever, sweetheart.

03:04.041 --> 03:05.041
It's, it's just until

03:05.041 --> 03:06.750
I finish this project.

03:06.750 --> 03:08.250
All right. I'll be right down.

03:08.250 --> 03:09.792
Down?

03:09.792 --> 03:11.000
Over.

03:11.000 --> 03:12.750
You know what I mean.

03:12.750 --> 03:13.875
Okay.
I'll see you a little later.

03:13.875 --> 03:15.083
I love you.

03:21.875 --> 03:23.667
MAN:
Good afternoon, Mrs. Phillips.

03:23.667 --> 03:24.959
Nice of you to join us.

03:24.959 --> 03:27.667
Are you aware that
your security company's

03:27.667 --> 03:29.959
deadline for getting
my bank on line

03:29.959 --> 03:31.625
was 23 hours ago?!

03:31.625 --> 03:33.875
Uh... Mr. Brisbane,
I-I did inform you

03:33.875 --> 03:36.125
that due to the age
of the building

03:36.125 --> 03:38.083
that we might encounter...

03:38.083 --> 03:40.125
The primary shareholders

03:40.125 --> 03:43.125
will be here for the opening
of the bank next Friday night.

03:43.125 --> 03:44.625
Mr. Brisbane,
as I have said,

03:44.625 --> 03:45.875
the system will not
have been tested,

03:45.875 --> 03:47.458
and I cannot in any kind
of good conscience...

03:47.458 --> 03:49.166
That party will take place,
Mrs. Phillips,

03:49.166 --> 03:50.959
with or without your consent.

03:50.959 --> 03:53.417
This is one of the most
complex installs...

03:53.417 --> 03:55.125
Hartmann, don't tell me
how to run my bank, all right?

03:55.125 --> 03:57.208
You work for me,

03:57.208 --> 03:58.708
remember?

03:58.708 --> 04:00.291
Now,

04:00.291 --> 04:03.250
when I turn around,
both of you will be gone.

04:03.250 --> 04:06.417
( chair squeaking  )

04:11.959 --> 04:16.500
( engines roaring  )

04:16.500 --> 04:19.500
ANNOUNCER:
And the race is under way!

04:19.500 --> 04:22.000
( indistinct announcement
over P.A. system  )

04:22.000 --> 04:25.500
( engines roaring  )

04:30.333 --> 04:32.667
ANNOUNCER:
Lap 13, and here's the lineup:

04:32.667 --> 04:34.708
Number 16, Eric the Obliterator,
still out in front,

04:34.708 --> 04:36.041
followed by 25...

04:36.041 --> 04:37.875
( engines roaring  )

04:41.375 --> 04:42.792
( engines roaring  )

04:46.166 --> 04:48.667
Number 11, Bad Chad,
is into the pits!

04:48.667 --> 04:51.625
( crowd cheering  )

04:51.625 --> 04:53.208
They go into turn number one.

04:53.208 --> 04:54.083
♪ ♪

05:00.208 --> 05:03.500
( engine roaring  )

05:03.500 --> 05:05.750
♪ ♪

05:05.750 --> 05:06.917
ANNOUNCER:
Here we go.

05:06.917 --> 05:09.333
Hey, retard!

05:09.333 --> 05:13.041
I'm losing the race 'cause you
don't know what you're doing!

05:13.041 --> 05:15.250
I can't believe Mom
made me hire you
as my lead mechanic.

05:15.250 --> 05:16.708
Damn!

05:16.708 --> 05:18.208
Done!

05:18.208 --> 05:19.875
ANNOUNCER:
They're burning rubber,

05:19.875 --> 05:21.208
they're bumping wheels,

05:21.208 --> 05:23.792
this is one scary race, folks.

05:23.792 --> 05:26.417
You better pray this works.

05:26.417 --> 05:28.875
( engine revving  )

05:28.875 --> 05:30.208
( shouting  )

05:30.208 --> 05:32.250
ANNOUNCER:
Number 11, Bad Chad,

05:32.250 --> 05:34.250
is out of the pits.

05:34.250 --> 05:36.959
Folks, it looks like
Number 11, Bad Chad,

05:36.959 --> 05:38.458
is finally out of the pits.

05:42.542 --> 05:45.458
ANNOUNCER: Stand by, folks, it
looks like Number 11, Bad Chad,
is finally out of the pits.

05:45.458 --> 05:47.250
Come on, man.
Come on. Come on.

05:47.250 --> 05:49.000
ANNOUNCER:
Chris the Crusher is pulling
tight into the turn.

05:49.000 --> 05:50.291
Bad Chad working his way
back into the pack.

05:55.250 --> 05:58.959
Whoa! Looks like that
front axle may have gone out.

05:58.959 --> 06:00.750
Number 11, Bad Chad,
is out of the race.

06:00.750 --> 06:02.458
Good job, dorkus!

06:02.458 --> 06:03.750
ANNOUNCER:
Now maybe C.D. can

06:03.750 --> 06:05.208
get back in this race.

06:05.208 --> 06:07.333
Gus!
He's blowing smoke here.

06:07.333 --> 06:08.708
He's got
exhaust problems, folks.

06:08.708 --> 06:10.291
His crews are
out there cleaning up.

06:10.291 --> 06:11.875
We got ourselves a yellow flag.

06:18.333 --> 06:20.917
( engines roaring  )

06:26.959 --> 06:29.125
There she is--
my leading lady.

06:29.125 --> 06:30.166
My star.

06:30.166 --> 06:33.417
Sound! Speed! And...

06:33.417 --> 06:34.792
action!

06:40.291 --> 06:42.250
( engine roars  )

06:44.208 --> 06:46.250
( carabiners clinking  )

06:53.291 --> 06:54.959
( engines roar  )

06:54.959 --> 06:56.333
Maddy!

06:58.500 --> 07:00.542
Maddy!

07:04.083 --> 07:05.542
Whoa!

07:05.542 --> 07:07.333
( engine roars  )

07:07.333 --> 07:08.875
Hey! Fart knocker!

07:08.875 --> 07:10.166
I'm going to kill you!

07:14.166 --> 07:15.667
Stop it! Don't!

07:18.291 --> 07:19.458
Cut it out! Cut it out!

07:19.458 --> 07:20.834
( groans  )

07:20.834 --> 07:21.875
Not so tight!

07:21.875 --> 07:22.834
Let go!

07:24.333 --> 07:26.708
Hi.
Oh, come on.

07:26.708 --> 07:28.208
Why don't you pick on
someone your own size?

07:28.208 --> 07:30.083
Oh, climber girl.

07:30.083 --> 07:32.667
( grunting  )

07:32.667 --> 07:35.667
Go contaminate
someone else!
( sniffs  )

07:35.667 --> 07:37.834
CHAD: Oh, look, here comes
Captain Cool.

07:37.834 --> 07:40.375
Loser number three.

07:40.375 --> 07:42.000
Look, um,
I'm having a barbecue

07:42.000 --> 07:43.542
at my house, if you guys
want to come over.

07:43.542 --> 07:45.041
Definitely.
Definitely.

07:45.041 --> 07:46.250
CHAD:
Oh, hey, uh...

07:46.250 --> 07:48.041
I don't know
if you heard,

07:48.041 --> 07:50.875
but Bad Chad picked up
a shift at your mama's bank.

07:50.875 --> 07:53.375
I'll be working with Lieutenant
Ferrell in security.

07:53.375 --> 07:56.083
One step closer to being a cop.

07:56.083 --> 07:57.834
Don't worry.

07:57.834 --> 08:00.166
Ferrell won't let
Bad Chad carry a weapon.

08:00.166 --> 08:01.375
He's an intern.

08:01.375 --> 08:04.250
Trainee, butt munch!

08:04.250 --> 08:06.917
Sorry, he's training
to be a butt munch!
Oh, I am going to...

08:06.917 --> 08:08.375
Doing a good job, too!
I'm going to brain you!

08:08.375 --> 08:09.417
Get over here!

08:09.417 --> 08:10.500
GUS:
I'm going to tell Mom!

08:10.500 --> 08:11.875
CHAD:
Hey! You are so dead!

08:11.875 --> 08:13.208
If I catch you,
I'm going to give you

08:13.208 --> 08:14.166
a purple nurple
so bad...

08:14.166 --> 08:15.959
He's so immature.

08:15.959 --> 08:18.125
Isn't he?

08:18.125 --> 08:20.792
ANNOUNCER:
Okay, folks, race number three

08:20.792 --> 08:22.333
will start in five minutes.

08:22.333 --> 08:24.083
So, let's get ready

08:24.083 --> 08:27.500
to step on the gas,
and let's kick some butt!

08:27.500 --> 08:28.959
It's race time!

08:28.959 --> 08:31.583
( cheering  )

08:31.583 --> 08:33.125
"Butt"?

08:33.125 --> 08:34.582
But what?

08:34.582 --> 08:36.417
Hey, Dad.
Hey, kiddo.

08:36.417 --> 08:37.417
What's up?

08:37.417 --> 08:38.958
Mom needs me to pick up Max

08:38.958 --> 08:40.250
from day care
again.

08:40.250 --> 08:41.417
( sighs  )

08:41.417 --> 08:43.000
It won't be forever, sweetie.

08:43.000 --> 08:45.000
All right, now you
sound like Mom.

08:45.000 --> 08:46.250
Oh, that's so terrible?

08:50.208 --> 08:54.291
You okay?

08:54.291 --> 08:56.625
Is this a, uh, new style
that the kids are sporting?

08:59.375 --> 09:00.625
Dad, don't freak out.

09:00.625 --> 09:02.542
When do I ever
freak out, Madeline?

09:02.542 --> 09:04.625
( pills rattling  )
It's just that there are

09:04.625 --> 09:06.708
a thousand other sports
that don't involve

09:06.708 --> 09:09.125
falling a hundred feet
to your death.

09:09.125 --> 09:11.542
Dad, you said standing
on the top of Mount Everest

09:11.542 --> 09:12.500
was the best day of your life.

09:12.500 --> 09:14.458
No. No.

09:14.458 --> 09:16.291
I said it was one of
the best days of my life.

09:16.291 --> 09:18.125
( playful growl  )
Look.

09:18.125 --> 09:20.000
See, I even wore
the hat you gave me.

09:23.125 --> 09:25.041
I just don't
understand

09:25.041 --> 09:26.708
what the problem is with me
trying to be like you.

09:26.708 --> 09:30.375
Do we have to discuss this
every day?

09:30.375 --> 09:32.291
Just till I turn 18.

09:32.291 --> 09:34.458
( growling  )

09:39.166 --> 09:42.417
Okay, race fans!
Here we are,
the last race of the day!

09:42.417 --> 09:44.417
Drivers, get in position.

09:44.417 --> 09:47.834
Hey, Mr. P., can I ask you
a very serious question?

09:47.834 --> 09:50.333
Only if you want
a very serious answer.

09:50.333 --> 09:52.000
Do ladies like guys

09:52.000 --> 09:54.417
who build stuff
with their hands,

09:54.417 --> 09:58.250
Or do they go for the nerds who
play computer games and stuff?

09:58.250 --> 10:02.208
Yo, what he means
is do women prefer
Hey, Dad.

10:02.208 --> 10:04.500
a low I.Q-Uber male who
only knows stuff about

10:04.500 --> 10:08.542
spark plugs,
or do they prefer a true artist

10:08.542 --> 10:10.041
who has both
sensitivity

10:10.041 --> 10:12.000
and a brain?

10:12.000 --> 10:14.000
That's a very
difficult question, boys,

10:14.000 --> 10:16.375
but I'm afraid
I'm not the one to ask.

10:16.375 --> 10:18.000
Hey, Madeline Rose!

10:18.000 --> 10:19.500
BOYS:
No, no, no, no.

10:19.500 --> 10:21.166
Dad, don't call me that.

10:23.166 --> 10:25.208
What are you doing?

10:25.208 --> 10:26.708
Nothing.
Nothing.

10:26.708 --> 10:28.208
Nothing. Nothing.

10:28.208 --> 10:29.208
( sizzling  )

10:29.208 --> 10:31.041
Ow! Ow! Ow! Ow!

10:31.041 --> 10:32.041
Ow! Ow!

10:32.041 --> 10:34.208
Ow! Ow! Ow! Ow! Ow!

10:34.208 --> 10:36.166
It's an old climber's trick.

10:36.166 --> 10:37.708
( groans  )

10:37.708 --> 10:40.458
Dude, you're going
to have a scar.

10:40.458 --> 10:41.834
Why do you get
all the cool stuff?

10:41.834 --> 10:43.708
You know, it's true,
women love scars.

10:43.708 --> 10:46.083
You know, this drives Maddy's
mom crazy-- check it out.

10:46.083 --> 10:47.625
Whoa.
That's gross.

10:47.625 --> 10:49.041
You can touch it if you want.

10:49.041 --> 10:50.417
Oh, is that
when you fell?

10:50.417 --> 10:51.208
Yep. 100-foot free fall.

10:52.375 --> 10:54.250
Okay, okay.

10:54.250 --> 10:55.667
Okay, stop touching.
( sighs  )

10:55.667 --> 10:57.041
Bad touch. Okay.

11:07.000 --> 11:08.417
Hey, stranger.

11:08.417 --> 11:10.708
Not you, too.

11:10.708 --> 11:12.291
Now, this
is a nutritious dinner.

11:12.291 --> 11:14.250
Please,

11:14.250 --> 11:15.583
don't give me a hard time.

11:17.417 --> 11:19.542
We just miss you.

11:19.542 --> 11:21.375
Especially Maddy.

11:23.750 --> 11:26.500
And I don't want to have
to set my alarm

11:26.500 --> 11:27.917
for the middle of the night

11:27.917 --> 11:29.375
just so I can have a date
with my wife.

11:31.667 --> 11:33.583
Would you like to go dancing?

11:33.583 --> 11:35.708
( chuckles  )

11:35.708 --> 11:39.208
( Tom hums, Molly laughs  )

11:43.458 --> 11:44.834
You know, I have to
go back to work.

11:44.834 --> 11:46.583
I can't... I really...
Oh, yeah.

11:46.583 --> 11:48.375
Okay, you have to do this first,
though, okay?

11:48.375 --> 11:50.458
( Molly chuckles  )

11:50.458 --> 11:52.291
( Tom groans  )

11:52.291 --> 11:53.625
Tom, come on,
stop messing around.

11:53.625 --> 11:55.125
I can't hold you up.

11:55.125 --> 11:57.166
I can't... Oh.

11:57.166 --> 11:59.625
Tom, what's going on?

11:59.625 --> 12:00.834
I can't feel my legs.

12:00.834 --> 12:02.291
What?

12:02.291 --> 12:03.375
Where does it hurt?

12:03.375 --> 12:06.458
Tom? Can you hear me?

12:06.458 --> 12:08.959
Tom?! Tom?!

12:13.458 --> 12:15.583
DOCTOR:
The injury probably occurred

12:15.583 --> 12:17.500
during his climbing accident.

12:17.500 --> 12:19.625
Well, there must be something
that you can do.

12:19.625 --> 12:20.917
I mean, isn't there any kind of

12:20.917 --> 12:23.333
emergency surgery
or anything?

12:23.333 --> 12:25.291
There's nothing we can do here.

12:25.291 --> 12:27.458
There is a private medical
facility in Denmark

12:27.458 --> 12:29.625
that has done testing
on this injury.

12:29.625 --> 12:31.500
Okay, then,
let's... let's go, then.

12:31.500 --> 12:34.166
It's considered experimental.

12:34.166 --> 12:35.542
Even though it's been
highly successful...

12:35.542 --> 12:37.250
We'll try any thing.

12:37.250 --> 12:39.375
Your insurance
won't cover it.

12:39.375 --> 12:41.166
How much?

12:41.166 --> 12:42.417
What?

12:42.417 --> 12:43.708
How much does
the surgery cost?

12:43.708 --> 12:45.542
We'll pay for it.

12:45.542 --> 12:47.041
$250,000.

12:51.500 --> 12:53.667
Okay, we... we'll pay it.
Mom...

12:53.667 --> 12:55.834
Tell... Mom, tell her
we'll pay it.

12:55.834 --> 12:57.291
Mom...

12:57.291 --> 13:00.750
we, we, we can pay it.

13:00.750 --> 13:03.542
Mom, tell her
we'll pay it, please?

13:03.542 --> 13:05.667
( crying  )

13:05.667 --> 13:07.542
GUS ( voice-over  ):
$250,000?

13:07.542 --> 13:09.166
Please tell her
we'll pay it.

13:09.166 --> 13:11.333
What happens if your dad
doesn't get the operation?

13:18.667 --> 13:20.708
We'll go door-to-door.

13:20.708 --> 13:23.625
Everyone loves your dad.
They'll give us money.

13:23.625 --> 13:25.458
I can sell my camera.

13:25.458 --> 13:26.542
MADDY:
It's $250,000,

13:26.542 --> 13:28.542
you guys.

13:28.542 --> 13:30.542
You know how much
money that is?

13:30.542 --> 13:32.625
I have a coin collection.

13:32.625 --> 13:34.375
They're rare.

13:42.291 --> 13:46.667
But... Well, what if I,
what if I borrow half,

13:46.667 --> 13:49.542
and then I can make...

13:49.542 --> 13:51.375
No, it doesn't exceed that.

13:53.583 --> 13:55.834
Personal collateral?

13:55.834 --> 14:00.625
Uh... we own a go-cart track.

14:00.625 --> 14:03.041
( sighs  )

14:03.041 --> 14:06.708
Let's cut to the chase,
shall we, Mrs. Phillips?

14:06.708 --> 14:09.750
You're not qualified for
a personal loan of this size.

14:09.750 --> 14:11.500
( Molly sighs  )

14:11.500 --> 14:13.667
I understand, but, uh,
my husband is sick and

14:13.667 --> 14:15.750
I was hoping...

14:15.750 --> 14:18.083
Yes. Yes, I'm aware of that,
Mrs. Phillips.

14:18.083 --> 14:22.250
Doesn't it mean anything
that I work for the bank?

14:22.250 --> 14:24.417
But you're freelance,
aren't you?

14:24.417 --> 14:25.542
Mm-hmm.

14:25.542 --> 14:28.083
From a security company.

14:32.000 --> 14:34.375
A security company, which,
under your guidance,

14:34.375 --> 14:36.792
has been unable
to provide my bank

14:36.792 --> 14:39.458
with a fully operational
security system

14:39.458 --> 14:40.667
in the allotted time

14:40.667 --> 14:43.166
stated in the contract.

14:45.375 --> 14:47.417
MOLLY:
Come on.

14:47.417 --> 14:49.250
Come on.

14:56.375 --> 14:58.333
Don't you have a heart?

14:58.333 --> 15:02.625
This is not an emotional issue,
Mrs. Phillips.

15:02.625 --> 15:05.625
A bank has no heart.

15:05.625 --> 15:09.083
Only paper in a vault.

15:15.959 --> 15:17.792
TOM ( voice-over  ):
Strange not being able to move.

15:17.792 --> 15:20.625
I've been staring
at the same spot

15:20.625 --> 15:23.792
on the ceiling
for the past three hours.

15:23.792 --> 15:26.500
Mom can't come up
with the money, Dad.

15:26.500 --> 15:30.041
I escaped death
on that climb, Maddy.

15:32.125 --> 15:35.917
20 feet from the summit,
my gear stuck,

15:35.917 --> 15:38.875
but there was this, this perfect
crack all the way up to the top.

15:38.875 --> 15:41.625
You free-climbed it?

15:41.625 --> 15:42.917
It was so easy.

15:42.917 --> 15:46.333
I lost concentration,
and I fell.

15:46.333 --> 15:47.959
But somebody or something
was looking out for me,

15:47.959 --> 15:50.834
so I could go home,
see you,

15:50.834 --> 15:54.667
get to know
what a great girl you are.

15:54.667 --> 15:56.917
In a way, that fall

15:56.917 --> 15:58.834
was the best thing that could
have happened to me.

16:01.708 --> 16:03.917
You know I'd do anything
for you.

16:03.917 --> 16:07.125
Dad, we'll come up
with the money. I promise.

16:07.125 --> 16:09.625
CD-ROM NARRATOR:
...and lined it with

16:09.625 --> 16:12.875
a 200-foot-high steel chamber,
which houses the Lion Safe.

16:12.875 --> 16:15.542
The system combines
the best of new technology

16:15.542 --> 16:17.792
and old, tried-and-true
security methods,

16:17.792 --> 16:20.708
making Harderbach Financial
the most secure a bank

16:20.708 --> 16:22.542
can be.
The entire system

16:22.542 --> 16:24.667
is run on a tri-generator,

16:24.667 --> 16:26.500
making power loss
a virtual impossibility,

16:26.500 --> 16:29.041
meaning the system
would remain safe

16:29.041 --> 16:31.583
even in the event
of a citywide blackout.

16:31.583 --> 16:34.458
The project began in the fall
of 2000 and is the largest,

16:34.458 --> 16:36.708
most technologically advanced
security install

16:36.708 --> 16:39.500
to date for any bank
in North America.

16:39.500 --> 16:41.542
The halls are lined
with hundreds

16:41.542 --> 16:43.583
of motion-sensitive cameras
whose images are fed back

16:43.583 --> 16:45.166
to a state-of-the-art
security booth.

16:45.166 --> 16:47.250
Until the system
has been fully tested,

16:47.250 --> 16:49.000
the halls will be patrolled
after-hours

16:49.000 --> 16:51.708
by highly trained attack dogs.

16:51.708 --> 16:53.917
This all leads to the Lion Safe.
The safe

16:53.917 --> 16:56.917
is suspended
nearly 100 feet off the ground

16:56.917 --> 16:59.375
and is equipped to hold over
$25 million

16:59.375 --> 17:01.250
in cash and gold bullion.

17:01.250 --> 17:03.375
Safety deposit boxes
line the walls of this chamber.

17:03.375 --> 17:05.583
Slated to be finished
in April of 2004...

17:05.583 --> 17:06.834
GUS:
Are you crazy?

17:06.834 --> 17:08.750
Oh, come on.
We can't rob a bank.

17:08.750 --> 17:10.750
We'll pay them back.

17:10.750 --> 17:12.583
How?

17:12.583 --> 17:13.916
I don't know.
I'll work. I'll do anything.

17:13.916 --> 17:15.375
You understand what

17:15.375 --> 17:16.625
happens if we get caught,
right?

17:16.625 --> 17:18.583
We go to jail forever.

17:18.583 --> 17:20.959
Like, until we're 21.

17:20.959 --> 17:23.625
No one will ever suspect us.

17:23.625 --> 17:25.458
Adults treat us like
we're five years old, anyway.

17:25.458 --> 17:27.583
How hard could it be?

17:27.583 --> 17:29.041
( voice-over  ):
Tomorrow, I'll go to work

17:29.041 --> 17:30.792
with my mom
and check out the bank.

17:30.792 --> 17:32.875
Meanwhile, Gus,

17:32.875 --> 17:34.959
you need to find out who
the architect is of the bank

17:34.959 --> 17:36.917
and see if you can get
a floor plan or a model.

17:36.917 --> 17:38.417
And, Austin,

17:38.417 --> 17:40.708
Austin'll take care of the dogs.

17:40.708 --> 17:42.583
What dogs?

17:42.583 --> 17:44.500
Rottweilers.

17:44.500 --> 17:46.041
Vicious killing dogs.

17:46.041 --> 17:49.041
MADDY:
Gus, come on.
This is serious.

17:49.041 --> 17:51.542
Tomorrow at the bank,
I'll try to check out
my mom's security system.

17:51.542 --> 17:53.792
GUARD:
Good morning, Mrs. Phillips.

17:53.792 --> 17:55.708
Who's that in the
car with you today?
MOLLY: It's my daughter.

17:55.708 --> 17:57.959
MADDY:
I'll try to take
as many pictures as I can.

17:57.959 --> 18:00.041
( shutter clicks  )

18:00.041 --> 18:02.166
You guys, I really need you.

18:03.959 --> 18:05.708
GUS:
All right.

18:05.708 --> 18:07.834
For Mr. P.

18:07.834 --> 18:09.208
For your dad.

18:13.041 --> 18:16.041
MOLLY:
Okay, Maddy, here we go.

18:17.959 --> 18:19.125
Maddy?

18:26.667 --> 18:28.208
( indistinct conversation  )

18:30.083 --> 18:32.041
( click  )

18:36.667 --> 18:37.542
( click  )

18:39.208 --> 18:41.333
( sighs  )

18:46.917 --> 18:49.000
( sniffs  )

18:54.542 --> 18:56.583
Do you have any idea
how fast you were going?

18:56.583 --> 18:57.625
Save it, pal.

18:57.625 --> 18:59.542
License and registration.

19:04.959 --> 19:09.041
That is the eye of God, Chad.

19:09.041 --> 19:10.834
Do you see these people?

19:10.834 --> 19:12.166
These are not people.

19:12.166 --> 19:14.208
These are

19:14.208 --> 19:17.041
snakes in paradise waiting
for your weakest moment.

19:17.041 --> 19:19.875
Any chance you give them.

19:19.875 --> 19:21.667
These people?

19:21.667 --> 19:22.708
Not to be trusted.

19:25.583 --> 19:26.834
Oh!

19:26.834 --> 19:29.250
My sweethearts.

19:29.250 --> 19:31.208
MOLLY:
Maddy?

19:31.208 --> 19:32.542
I love that you wanted

19:32.542 --> 19:33.959
to come to work with me
today, sweetheart,

19:33.959 --> 19:35.417
but I have a lot of work to do.

19:35.417 --> 19:37.000
So I kind of need you
to keep up, okay?

19:37.000 --> 19:38.083
Can I see the safe?

19:38.083 --> 19:39.208
That's just the old safe.

19:39.208 --> 19:40.708
The real one's upstairs.

19:40.708 --> 19:43.041
What are those?

19:43.041 --> 19:44.083
That's a motion detector.

19:44.083 --> 19:45.708
Can I see the new safe?

19:45.708 --> 19:48.041
And, if Miss Fancy-Pants
Phillips over there

19:48.041 --> 19:50.083
would've listened to me

19:50.083 --> 19:53.375
we wouldn't need all this
high-tech flim-flammery.

19:53.375 --> 19:57.542
The dogs...!
( dogs whimpering  )

19:57.542 --> 20:00.083
...the dogs would have done
all the work.

20:00.083 --> 20:03.583
The dogs and my black belt.

20:07.083 --> 20:09.583
( martial arts yells  )

20:09.583 --> 20:11.959
( back cracking, groans  )

20:11.959 --> 20:14.000
Back to the monitor,
maggot!

20:14.000 --> 20:16.250
Your office upstairs?

20:16.250 --> 20:18.041
Yeah. I need to be
near the safe.

20:18.041 --> 20:19.291
( whirring  )

20:19.291 --> 20:20.917
Whoa.

20:20.917 --> 20:22.792
That thing looks
like it's alive.

20:22.792 --> 20:25.166
MOLLY:
It's got a built-in motion
detector.

20:25.166 --> 20:27.417
I mean, the guards can't watch
all hundred cameras at
the same time,

20:27.417 --> 20:29.959
so when the camera
picks up movement,
then the light goes on

20:29.959 --> 20:31.291
and they can see us.

20:31.291 --> 20:33.250
Watch. Just stay
completely still.

20:36.166 --> 20:37.625
CHAD:
Ah, climber girl.

20:44.000 --> 20:45.291
That's pretty cool.

20:45.291 --> 20:46.583
( elevator bell dings  )

20:52.792 --> 20:54.750
HARTMANN:
Well, they better fix

20:54.750 --> 20:57.000
the ISP, 'cause that whole
side of the building is S.O.L.

20:57.000 --> 20:58.750
Molly...Oh.

20:58.750 --> 21:00.250
I didn't think
you were coming in today.

21:00.250 --> 21:02.792
Oh, well, the party is Friday,

21:02.792 --> 21:05.250
so I wanted to make sure the
system is as close as possible.

21:05.250 --> 21:08.583
Yeah. Listen, uh, I spoke
with Brisbane about the loan,

21:08.583 --> 21:11.333
and he just wouldn't budge.
I'm really sorry.

21:11.333 --> 21:14.500
MOLLY:
Oh, God. Well, we'll have
to figure out some other way.

21:14.500 --> 21:17.291
Would you like a tour?
MOLLY:
Oh, Alan, that's really...

21:17.291 --> 21:19.000
Yeah! That'd be awesome.

21:19.000 --> 21:20.583
Well, great.
We'll start this way.

21:20.583 --> 21:22.375
Don't worry.
I'll take good care of her.

21:22.375 --> 21:24.083
Take care of that for me,
would you?

21:24.083 --> 21:25.041
Now, we're going
to begin...

21:30.959 --> 21:32.333
MAN:
I paid that phone bill!

21:32.333 --> 21:35.208
I paid that phone bill
last week!

21:37.917 --> 21:40.375
Hi.
My name's Austin.

21:40.375 --> 21:42.542
Easy!

21:42.542 --> 21:45.375
My name's Austin, and, uh,
I make movies... director.

21:45.375 --> 21:48.375
Really?

21:48.375 --> 21:50.500
How may I help you?

21:50.500 --> 21:52.667
Okay, I got this dog
for my birthday.

21:52.667 --> 21:54.625
And I was hoping I could
use him as a stunt dog--

21:54.625 --> 21:56.125
What kind of dog do you have?

21:56.125 --> 21:57.875
A Budweiser?

21:57.875 --> 21:59.875
Rottweiler?

21:59.875 --> 22:01.583
Yeah.

22:01.583 --> 22:03.959
I just happen to be
a Rottweiler expert.

22:03.959 --> 22:07.834
There is a really nice boy here
who's going to write an essay

22:07.834 --> 22:09.375
about the design of the

22:09.375 --> 22:12.375
Harderbach Financial
building,

22:12.375 --> 22:14.792
and he needs
a floor-plan drawing

22:14.792 --> 22:18.291
that he can use
as a visual aid for his essay.

22:18.291 --> 22:20.083
MAN:
Are you freakin' nuts?!

22:20.083 --> 22:22.792
You can't give bank
floor plans to a kid!

22:22.792 --> 22:24.792
You're just...!

22:24.792 --> 22:28.542
Normally, he's very nice.

22:28.542 --> 22:29.959
But it's a little more
difficult with banks.

22:29.959 --> 22:31.875
I mean,

22:31.875 --> 22:34.041
imagine if you were
a bank robber.

22:34.041 --> 22:35.250
( laughs  )

22:35.250 --> 22:37.542
( weak chuckle  )

22:37.542 --> 22:40.417
It's just that last time
I got a C on my essay because

22:40.417 --> 22:42.083
I didn't have
any visual aids.

22:42.083 --> 22:43.291
And my stepdad, he...

22:43.291 --> 22:47.417
well, he gets a little...

22:47.417 --> 22:50.458
( gasps  ):
Oh...

22:54.083 --> 22:56.250
You stay here.

22:59.917 --> 23:01.125
( chuckles  )

23:08.125 --> 23:09.917
HARTMANN:
I know you can't see it now,

23:09.917 --> 23:12.000
but by the party, we
are hoping it's primo.

23:12.000 --> 23:14.458
And down here is
the security room.

23:14.458 --> 23:16.250
Ultra high-tech and cool.
Your mom designed that, too.

23:16.250 --> 23:17.792
( polite laugh  )

23:17.792 --> 23:19.792
You might notice the keypads,
which are designed

23:19.792 --> 23:23.208
to keep people out of the
important areas of the bank.

23:23.208 --> 23:24.291
Who has the codes to all these?

23:24.291 --> 23:26.125
Oh, uh, they're different

23:26.125 --> 23:27.250
from room to room.

23:27.250 --> 23:29.291
But, uh, I have a code

23:29.291 --> 23:30.959
that is good
for the whole building.

23:30.959 --> 23:32.458
Cool.

23:32.458 --> 23:33.667
Come on.

23:40.125 --> 23:43.500
D-E-N-I-R-O.

23:43.500 --> 23:46.125
"Deniro."

23:49.959 --> 23:53.667
Oh, look at that view.

23:53.667 --> 23:55.834
This is the coolest office
in the building.

23:55.834 --> 23:58.083
It belongs to the big cheese,
Mr. Brisbane.

23:58.083 --> 23:59.458
Check this out.

23:59.458 --> 24:00.917
( keyboard clicks  )

24:00.917 --> 24:02.041
Huh?

24:02.041 --> 24:04.250
Huh? Huh, and get this:

24:04.250 --> 24:06.375
Your mom has rigged it

24:06.375 --> 24:09.000
so you can control all
the cameras from right here.

24:11.333 --> 24:12.875
( imitating De Niro  ):
You talking to me?

24:12.875 --> 24:15.250
Huh?

24:15.250 --> 24:16.166
Are you talking to me?

24:19.166 --> 24:20.250
It's De Niro.

24:20.250 --> 24:22.041
I still do some acting.

24:22.041 --> 24:24.375
This bank manager thing
is just temporary.

24:24.375 --> 24:26.041
Hey, come on. You try it.

24:26.041 --> 24:27.041
Uh...

24:28.875 --> 24:30.834
I don't know what to say.

24:30.834 --> 24:33.041
Say anything.

24:33.041 --> 24:34.041
Hi.

24:34.041 --> 24:35.875
Disgusting.

24:35.875 --> 24:37.041
Good!

24:41.375 --> 24:43.291
( zapping  )

24:43.291 --> 24:45.000
( yells  )

24:47.041 --> 24:49.208
Oh.

24:49.208 --> 24:50.917
HARTMANN:
In this room there's a tunnel

24:50.917 --> 24:52.542
that leads to the safe.

24:52.542 --> 24:54.333
I can only tell you a little bit
about the safe.

24:54.333 --> 24:56.375
Only your mom understands
the whole thing.

24:56.375 --> 24:57.917
I mean, after all,
she designed it.

24:57.917 --> 24:58.959
( barking  )

24:58.959 --> 25:01.291
Oh, no! Look out.

25:01.291 --> 25:03.583
( panting  )

25:03.583 --> 25:05.417
I can't wait until we
get rid of these things.

25:05.417 --> 25:06.542
They get me every time.

25:06.542 --> 25:08.250
Down!

25:08.250 --> 25:11.625
Shh!

25:11.625 --> 25:14.542
Rottweilers respond
to German commands only!

25:14.542 --> 25:17.375
( barking  )

25:17.375 --> 25:19.417
Ausfahrt, Killer! Ausfahrt!

25:19.417 --> 25:21.458
Say, "Ausfahrt," kid.

25:21.458 --> 25:23.458
Do it!
Or he'll rip your throat out!

25:23.458 --> 25:25.083
Ass fart!

25:25.083 --> 25:27.041
Ausfahrt!

25:27.041 --> 25:29.250
You must show them respect!

25:29.250 --> 25:31.458
Ouch fart!

25:31.458 --> 25:33.250
( imitates buzzer  )

25:33.250 --> 25:35.625
Wrong answer.

25:38.458 --> 25:39.917
( barking  )

25:39.917 --> 25:43.041
Ass fart! Ass fart!

25:43.041 --> 25:44.083
( chuckles  )
Down!

25:44.083 --> 25:46.417
Go away, Ass fart!

25:50.667 --> 25:51.792
( grunts  )

26:02.792 --> 26:05.166
Get out of here, kid,
before I turn him loose on you!

26:05.166 --> 26:08.458
No respect!

26:08.458 --> 26:11.417
Come on, baby! Come on! Woof!

26:11.417 --> 26:13.959
♪ ♪

26:24.750 --> 26:26.708
♪ ♪

26:35.792 --> 26:37.959
Don't ever tell anybody
where you got it.

26:37.959 --> 26:40.250
I would never.
Thank you.

26:40.250 --> 26:43.166
♪ ♪

26:51.291 --> 26:53.708
♪ ♪

27:02.667 --> 27:03.917
They're going to send out
a search party for me

27:03.917 --> 27:05.834
if I don't get back to work,

27:05.834 --> 27:07.208
so can you find your way back
to your mom's office?

27:07.208 --> 27:09.250
Yeah.
Thanks, Mr. Hartmann.

27:09.250 --> 27:10.542
Okay. Bye.

27:10.542 --> 27:11.583
I'll see you tomorrow.

27:11.583 --> 27:12.708
Mr. Hartmann?

27:12.708 --> 27:14.792
Hmm?

27:14.792 --> 27:17.208
I think you make
a really good actor.

27:17.208 --> 27:18.333
Thanks.

27:24.542 --> 27:26.125
MADDY:
Okay, so the party's
gonna be in two days.

27:26.125 --> 27:27.583
That's when we'll hit the bank.

27:27.583 --> 27:29.333
Austin, how did it go
with the dogs?

27:29.333 --> 27:31.041
AUSTIN:
The dogs, they're under control.

27:31.041 --> 27:33.041
MADDY:
Gus, the model
looks pretty cool.

27:33.041 --> 27:34.458
GUS:
It was a piece of cake.

27:34.458 --> 27:36.375
I thought that secretary
was gonna adopt me.

27:36.375 --> 27:37.375
( Maddy chuckles  )

27:46.375 --> 27:49.250
Do you guys think
we could do it?

27:49.250 --> 27:50.750
Do really think we could
get the money?

27:50.750 --> 27:52.333
Are you kidding?
Of course.

27:52.333 --> 27:53.875
Yeah, of course.

27:53.875 --> 27:56.417
I mean, you're, like,
the best climber

27:56.417 --> 27:57.750
in the whole state.

27:57.750 --> 27:59.417
Yeah, and
Austin's, like,

27:59.417 --> 28:00.667
some freak-of-nature
computer genius.

28:00.667 --> 28:03.583
Yeah, and Gus is,
like, what?

28:03.583 --> 28:05.417
( belches loudly  )

28:05.417 --> 28:08.458
( laughs  )

28:08.458 --> 28:10.625
Gus is disgusting.

28:10.625 --> 28:12.250
MADDY:
Austin, this should be

28:12.250 --> 28:14.458
exactly the height of
the gate at the bank.

28:14.458 --> 28:15.542
Watch carefully, okay?

28:22.083 --> 28:23.542
Okay, Austin, your turn.

28:28.041 --> 28:30.375
GUS:
The cart doesn't control you.

28:30.375 --> 28:32.458
You control the cart.

28:32.458 --> 28:34.583
Go.I got it!

28:37.458 --> 28:41.125
Whoa! Yikes! Whoa! Whoa!

28:41.125 --> 28:45.125
( panicked cries  )

28:45.125 --> 28:47.458
Is there any way
you can make them

28:47.458 --> 28:49.959
quieter and faster?

28:56.208 --> 28:57.792
AUSTIN:
Do you want a window,

28:57.792 --> 28:59.834
or an aisle?

29:02.375 --> 29:05.458
♪ ♪

29:12.250 --> 29:14.708
A hundred P.S.I. of pure Nos.

29:22.333 --> 29:25.333
♪ ♪

29:30.333 --> 29:34.083
( whirring  )

29:34.083 --> 29:36.875
Okay. Work for your daddy.

29:38.667 --> 29:42.291
( engine revving  )

29:42.291 --> 29:44.667
( switch clicks,
deep rumbling)

29:44.667 --> 29:46.125
It worked! I'm a genius!

29:46.125 --> 29:48.333
But how am I gonna stop?

29:48.333 --> 29:50.667
Maybe I'm not a genius!

29:50.667 --> 29:52.792
( yells  )

30:00.834 --> 30:02.750
( engine sputters  )

30:02.750 --> 30:03.542
( groans and sighs  )

30:06.708 --> 30:08.708
MADDY:
Mr. Hartmann's
a really nice guy--

30:08.708 --> 30:10.667
Do you have your script?

30:10.667 --> 30:12.542
AUSTIN:
I'm the director.
I'm always prepared.

30:12.542 --> 30:14.250
GUS ( mocking  ):
I'm always prepared.

30:14.250 --> 30:15.792
MADDY:
Austin, you just have to get him

30:15.792 --> 30:17.208
to say to turn the alarm off.

30:17.208 --> 30:19.625
AUSTIN:
Off. I know. I know.

30:19.625 --> 30:21.834
Come on, hurry up.

30:21.834 --> 30:23.417
I'm coming.

30:23.417 --> 30:25.458
Wait for me!

30:25.458 --> 30:27.208
HARTMANN:
Take it easy.

30:27.208 --> 30:28.542
( imitating De Niro  ):
Take it easy.

30:28.542 --> 30:29.542
Take it easy.

30:29.542 --> 30:32.333
All right. Here...

30:32.333 --> 30:33.625
Maddy is playing a girl
who is home alone

30:33.625 --> 30:34.708
and scared of the dark.

30:34.708 --> 30:36.583
And you play her dad,

30:36.583 --> 30:38.500
who walks in just
as the alarm blares.

30:38.500 --> 30:42.583
Whoa, wh-wh-wh-what
do I do for a living?

30:42.583 --> 30:45.291
I'm glad you asked.

30:45.291 --> 30:48.667
You work for a specialized
branch of the CIA.

30:48.667 --> 30:50.542
Ooh...
I like that.

30:50.542 --> 30:52.583
I've always wanted
to play an assassin.

30:52.583 --> 30:54.291
Well, here's
your chance.

30:54.291 --> 30:56.792
You are a CIA assassin.

30:56.792 --> 30:57.792
( exhales sharply  )

30:57.792 --> 31:00.875
Uh... can I get a water, please?

31:00.875 --> 31:02.417
Can I talk to you for a second?
Over here?

31:02.417 --> 31:03.458
( murmurs  )

31:03.458 --> 31:06.500
Um... okay.

31:06.500 --> 31:08.917
Now, which is stronger?

31:08.917 --> 31:10.417
Hair?

31:10.417 --> 31:12.250
Or no hair?

31:12.250 --> 31:13.417
( chuckles softly  )

